snippet.textDisplay: I lived outside Atlanta from '99-'06.  Mitch would play The Punchline and I'd send out emails to a group of friends whenever someone I liked was playing to try to get people to go.....during that time I got to see Jim Gaffigan, Craig Robinson, Louis Black, Dave Attell, Jeff Dunham, John Witherspoon, Greg Fitzsimmons, and others.  The friends who saw Mitch for the first time almost got on their knees and thanked me for inviting them.  People in the audience would actually yell out jokes they wanted to hear him tell.  If he played a weekend, I'd got see two shows and would for Attell as well.  Also Mitch opened for Dave Attell and Louis Black when the Comedy Central tour came through and got to see that show at The Tabernacle.  It was great but there's just something about seeing a show in a club.  Miss him every day.
snippet.textOriginal: I lived outside Atlanta from '99-'06.  Mitch would play The Punchline and I'd send out emails to a group of friends whenever someone I liked was playing to try to get people to go.....during that time I got to see Jim Gaffigan, Craig Robinson, Louis Black, Dave Attell, Jeff Dunham, John Witherspoon, Greg Fitzsimmons, and others.  The friends who saw Mitch for the first time almost got on their knees and thanked me for inviting them.  People in the audience would actually yell out jokes they wanted to hear him tell.  If he played a weekend, I'd got see two shows and would for Attell as well.  Also Mitch opened for Dave Attell and Louis Black when the Comedy Central tour came through and got to see that show at The Tabernacle.  It was great but there's just something about seeing a show in a club.  Miss him every day.

snippet.textDisplay:
When you go to a restaurant on the weekends and it’s busy so they start a waiting list, they say, "Dufrene, party of two, table ready for Dufrene, party of two."
And if no one answers they’ll say the name again: "Dufrene, party of two."
But then if no one answers, they’ll move on to the next name. "Bush, party of three."
Yeah, but what happened to the Dufrenes? No one seems to care. Who can eat at a time like this? People are missing. You people are selfish. The Dufrenes are in someone’s trunk right now, with duct tape over their mouths. And they’re hungry. Dufrene, search party of two.
